    "description": "Are you a skilled Curriculum Developer looking for your next big career move? upGrad Asia Pacific Associates in Vadodara offers you the perfect platform to grow professionally and personally.\n\nAbout upGrad Asia Pacific Associates:\nupGrad Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Design formative and summative assessments aligned to learning objectives\n• Monitor student progress and provide timely feedback\n• Utilize technology and digital tools to enhance learning outcomes\n• Create curriculum-aligned learning materials and assessments\n• Participate in teacher training and professional development programs\n• Collaborate with faculty on curriculum development initiatives\n• Maintain student records and prepare progress reports\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• BPharm / MPharm / PharmD\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in CBSE/ICSE Standards\n• Proficiency in Bloom's Taxonomy\n• Proficiency in Classroom Management\n• Proficiency in Zoom/Teams\n• Proficiency in Content Creation\n• Proficiency in Communication Skills\n• Proficiency in Pedagogy\n• Proficiency in Lesson Planning\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Referral bonus program\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vadodara, Gujarat, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with upGrad Asia Pacific Associates!",
